<TITLE> Tarique departure delayed: lawyer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 10 (bdnews24.com)BNP senior joint secretary general Tarique Rahman's departure for the UK has been postponed, his lawyer complaining that he could not leave Wednesday as scheduled because of "obstructions" created by the government. However, BNP leader Hannan Shah told reporters earlier in the evening that detained former prime minister Khaleda Zia wished to see her ailing son before he went. "I have just now got information that Tarique Rahman's going abroad has been postponed." "Khaleda Zia wants to see her ailing son. A decision in this regard will be known tomorrow (Thursday)." Tarique's lawyer Ahmed Azam Khan told reporters at BSMMU Hospital late Wednesday night: "Tarique Rahman was ready to fly to the UK on a Singapore Airlines flight at 11.55pm." "But due to obstructions by the government, he could not go." He said: "Tickets were confirmed on Singapore airlines for Tarique, his wife and daughter. We let the government know in the early afternoon." "But we didn't get any response from them even up to now (10pm). "The reporting time for the flight was 10pm. But Tarique cannot move, even to travel to the airport without the government's permission." bdnews24.
